red tattoos do you have one and how did it heal i got one about a month ago on the back of my leg its the queen of hearts from disney's alice in wonderland and the red won't heal its stayed kinda dry and tough i'm not sure how to get it to heal red allergies happen it's not very common but there are those of us out there that have them when i have any red done on my body and trust me i try to stay away from it it takes forever to heal is dry super scabby and itches for weeks the skin around the area usually also gets red and swollen but i've got an awesome dr who will prescribe me with amoxicillian when i know i'm getting red work done usually after i loose a little ink depending on how bad my reaction is the best thing to do is see your artist and let them know you had an ink reaction lotion lotion lotion try to keep it clean and moisturized see a doctor they may give you something different to put on it which might not be the best for the tattoo but hey at this point your most likely going to loose ink anyways better to get it healed up so your skin can rest before you decide to do any touch up work Tattoo Eczema Psoriasis Conjunctivitis Scarification Group A streptococcal infection Body piercing Fecal incontinence Stomach cancer Manicure Wound Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Tuberculosis Dragon Booster Alice's Adventures in Wonderland Medicine Aloe Mast cell Skin Tocopherol Mouth ulcer Urinary incontinence Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Acne Scabies Otitis externa Dyspareunia Massage Phoebe Halliwell Rash Medical prescription Shaving Hay fever Clomipramine Paint The Doctor Dances Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Scar Dandruff Cephalexin First aid Cliff Richard Traumatic brain injury Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Irezumi House dust mite Mercury (element) Radiation therapy Queen (band) Cellulitis Diving suit Snooker YuYu Hakusho Cosmetics Homeopathy Sunscreen Father's Day (Doctor Who) Billboard Hot 100 Smallville (Season 4) Mosquito Spina bifida Doxepin Weather l